name: curr_bw
doc: Sets the bandwidth for AC current measurements.

name: curr_null_enable
doc: Enables or disables the null function for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_null_value
doc: Sets the null value for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_null_value
doc: Sets the null value for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_range
doc: Selects a fixed measurement range for AC or DC current measurements on the 3 A terminals.

name: curr_range_auto
doc: Disables or enables autoranging for AC or DC current measurements. Autoranging is convenient because it automatically selects the range for each measurement based on the input signal. Did not implement ONCE

name: curr_nplc
doc:
Sets the integration time in number of power line cycles (PLC) for DC current measurements. Integration
time is the period that the instrument's analog-to-digital (A/D) converter samples the input signal for a
measurement. A longer integration time gives better measurement resolution but slower measurement
speed.

name: curr_res
doc: Selects the measurement resolution for DC current measurements. Specify the resolution in the same units as the selected measurement function, not in number of digits.

name: meas_cap
doc:
Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for capacitance measurements
and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instrument's output
buffer.

name: meas_curr
doc: Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for AC or DC current measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.

name: meas_volt
doc: Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for AC or DC voltage measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.
